news.title: Union home minister chairs high-level meeting on Delhi master plan 2041
news.para: Union Home Minister Amit Shah led a high-level meeting to assess the Delhi Master Plan 2041, with Delhi Chief Minister Rekha Gupta and Union Minister Manohar Lal Khattar participating. The meeting, following a prior review, addressed the plan submitted by the DDA in April 2023, which is still awaiting final approval after receiving the LG's endorsement.

news.title: PropShare Titania SM REIT ₹473 crore issue to open on July 21
news.para: Property Share Investment Trust has introduced PropShare Titania, their second SM REIT scheme, aiming to raise up to ₹473 crore. The IPO, featuring a fresh issue of units priced between ₹10 lakh and ₹10.6 lakh, will be open for subscription from July 21 to July 25, 2025.

news.title: UK's Barratt Redrow misses home completion target, warns of 'fragile' buyer confidence
news.para: Barratt Redrow, Britain's largest homebuilder, faced a setback as it missed its annual home completion forecast, reporting 16,565 completions against the projected 16,800-17,200. This shortfall, coupled with fragile buyer confidence amid a faltering economy, sent the company's shares plummeting. The London market proved particularly weak, impacting overall performance.

news.title: The Executive Centre is said to seek ₹2,600 crore for India IPO
news.para: The Executive Centre is planning an initial public offering in Mumbai that may raise 26 billion rupees ($303 million), according to people familiar with the matter, to capitalize on the rising demand for workspace in the country.

news.title: Villagers oppose proposed cement plant in Mansa village
news.para: Residents of Talwandi Aklia and Karamgarh Autanwali protested against a proposed cement plant. The Punjab Pollution Control Board held a public hearing. Villagers fear environmental hazards from the red category industry. The Public Action Committee mobilized the opposition. JSW Cement Limited plans a 6 MTPA plant. Concerns were raised about the project's impact.

news.title: Karnataka: Note to urban development department offers hope to B khata property owners
news.para: The note is based on a letter written by former president of BJP Bengaluru South NR Ramesh. “Most of the buildings are constructed on B khata properties.

news.title: Belagavi civic body collects record ₹44.7 crore property tax in Q1 FY26
news.para: Belagavi City Corporation targets Rs 75 crore in property tax for fiscal year 2025-26. The corporation collected Rs 44.7 crore in the first quarter. This was due to a 5% rebate scheme. The BCC focuses on unauthorized buildings and tax defaulters. Owners of unlawful constructions must pay a single tax. The corporation has initiated recovery measures for chronic defaulters.

news.title: WeWork India gets Sebi's nod for IPO
news.para: WeWork India has received SEBI's nod for its IPO. The IPO is entirely an offer for sale of 4.37 crore equity shares. Selling shareholders include Embassy Buildcon LLP and 1 Ariel Way Tenant. WeWork India reported a consolidated income of ₹1,737.16 crore for FY24. The company's total borrowings stood at ₹616.90 crore in FY24.

news.title: Noida looks for vertical scale-up of firefight tech as buildings get taller
news.para: Noida's fire department is enhancing its capabilities with high-pressure foam extinguishers, tested at the 74-storey Supertech Supernova tower, to combat highrise fires effectively. The Compressed Air Foam System (CAFS) maintains pressure at extreme heights, addressing challenges posed by reduced water pressure. Additionally, a fire safety expo showcased advanced firefighting suits and air-purifying helmets, improving safety measures.

news.title: Oberoi Realty-led consortium wins bid for Hotel Horizon in ₹919 crore resolution plan
news.para: Oberoi Realty, along with Shree Naman Developers and JM Financial Properties, has been chosen as the resolution applicant for Hotel Horizon (HHPL) through the IBC process. The consortium's resolution plan, approved by the creditors, involves a ₹919 crore payment to settle all dues.

news.title: CM instructed UDD to expedite Maan-Mhalunge TP scheme clearance: PMRDA officials
news.para: Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis has directed the urban development department to expedite the clearance of the Maan-Mhalunge town planning scheme in Hinjewadi. This instruction came during a review meeting addressing civic and infrastructure issues.

news.title: Delhi master plan 2041 may be sent back to drawing board
news.para: Delhi's Master Plan 2041, designed to guide the capital's urban development, is under review by the Delhi government after being submitted to the Centre in April 2023. The Delhi government held a closed-door meeting to review various provisions of the document.

news.title: Elan group raises ₹250 crore from Piramal Finance
news.para: Elan Group, a Gurgaon-based developer, has secured Rs 250 crore from Piramal Finance. The funding will support the construction of a commercial project in Gurgaon. This follows a Rs 1,200 crore funding from Kotak Real Estate Fund last year. Elan Group will use the funds to expedite its regional projects. The company's portfolio includes 15 projects across various segments.

news.title: Lucknow development body orders probe into unauthorised construction
news.para: The Lucknow Development Authority is investigating unauthorized construction in Gomtinagar's Vinamra Khand, prompted by a neighbor's complaints. Yamini Mathur alleges violations of the approved building plan, including encroachment on setback areas.

news.title: After 16 years, Gujarat drafts new policy to boost township projects
news.para: Gujarat is overhauling its urban housing strategy with a new township policy, aiming to incentivize organized and affordable housing. The revised policy addresses shortcomings of the 2009 version by offering incentives like relaxed FSI and tax breaks. It also ensures better alignment with urban development plans to attract real estate developers for large-scale, self-sustained townships.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body receives 49,000 suggestions & objections to its draft of revised development plan
news.para: Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation finished taking suggestions for the revised development plan. They received 49,000 responses from residents. A committee will review these submissions. The draft plan was earlier approved on May 16. Residents and politicians opposed road networks and amenity reservations. Objections were raised against the High Capacity Mass Transit Route.

news.title: Maharashtra govt panel proposes 10% extra carpet area for housing societies going for self-redevelopment
news.para: Mumbai residents may soon get more space in self-redeveloped homes. A government committee suggests a 10% increase in carpet area. This encourages residents to redevelop their buildings independently. The scheme could extend to cluster redevelopment projects. Slum dwellers are also included in the proposal. The government is considering financial support for these projects.

news.title: China Vanke expects up to $1.7 billion net loss in H1 2025
news.para: China Vanke, a state-backed property developer, anticipates a significant net loss. The expected loss is up to 12 billion yuan for the first half of the year. This is due to a drop in project settlements and low profit margins. The company is also making extra provisions. Vanke had a senior management reshuffle earlier this year.

news.title: China's new home prices in June fall at fastest monthly pace in eight months
news.para: New data reveals that China's home prices declined in June. This is the fastest monthly drop in eight months. The property sector continues to weigh on economic growth. Policymakers are struggling to revive demand. The State Council plans a nationwide survey of land and projects. Current support measures include easing restrictions and reducing mortgage rates.

news.title: Illegal constructions will not be spared, strict action against erring officials: Maharashtra deputy CM
news.para: Maharashtra government is committed to cracking down on illegal constructions, Deputy CM Eknath Shinde affirmed in the assembly. Instructions will be issued to the BMC to list unauthorized structures, and officials found complicit will face strict action. Demolition drives, paused due to monsoon, will resume, with action taken under the MRTP Act.
